                          <desc>Calendar of the year, with the text of <locus target="#126v" facs="129">fol. 126v</locus> erased to draw the Crucifixion</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <locus target="#127v" facs="130">Fol. 127v</locus>
                           <desc>The Ethiopic alphabet from ሀ to ሒ</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                          <locus target="#67v" facs="070">Fol. 67v</locus>
                          <desc>An overlooked line of text has been inserted in the upper margin and a symbol (an ornate + sign) markes the place where the text should be read</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                          <locus target="#5v #6r #10v #11r #13v #14r" facs="008 013 016">Fols. 5v, 6r, 10v, 11r, 13v, 14r</locus>
                          <desc>etc., the scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                          Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size.
                          But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line</desc>
                          </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                          <locus target="#52r" facs="054">Fol. 52r</locus>
                          <desc>etc., this scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line</desc>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="a4">
                            <locus target="#13r #15v #24r #24v #26r #27r #86v #109v" facs="015 018 026 027 028 029 089 112">Fols. 13r, 15v, 24r, 24v, 26r, 27r, 86v, 109v</locus>
                            <desc>Overlooked lines of text have been inserted between lines</desc>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e5">
                            <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus>
                            <desc>Unintelligible note</desc>
                          </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
